msgid "Using Custom Logos in |at|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/custom_rebranding.rst:14
msgid ""
"Custom rebranding was added to |at| with version 2.4.0 and is available "
"to Enterprise-level license holders."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/custom_rebranding.rst:16
msgid ""
"To set up a custom logo, you must upload a file that you create called "
"``custom_console_logo.png`` into the "
"``/var/lib/awx/public/static/assets/`` directory. For the custom logo to "
"look its best, use a ``.png`` file with a transparent background."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/custom_rebranding.rst:18
msgid ""
"Next, either create a ``/var/lib/awx/public/static/local_settings.json`` "
"file or add the following variable to the ``local_settings.json`` file if"
" it already exists:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/custom_rebranding.rst:24
msgid ""
"Setting the ``custom_logo`` variable to ``false`` (or not setting it at "
"all), results in the appearance of the standard |at| logo."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/custom_rebranding.rst:28
msgid ""
"If you cannot see the image in the |at| login dialog box after moving it "
"into the ``assets`` directory, you must ``chown`` this file as the "
"\"awx\" user, ``chmod`` this file as ``755`` for the correct permissions,"
" and fix any SELinux labeling (if you are on |rhel| or CentOS, or another"
" OS that uses SELinux).  You can do this by using the ``wget`` or ``scp``"
" commands and directly accessing the ``assets`` directory "
"(``/var/lib/awx/public/static/assets/``)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/custom_rebranding.rst:30
msgid ""
"If needed, you can add specific information (such as a legal notice or a "
"disclaimer) to a text box in the login modal by adding "
"``\"custom_login_info\": \"your notice content here‚Äù`` to the object "
"(``/var/lib/awx/public/static/local_settings.json``).  Any content added "
"must be in plain text, as custom HTML or other markup languages are not "
"supported.  If multiple paragraphs of text are needed, new lines "
"(paragraphs) must be escaped as ``\\n`` within the block of text, instead"
" of being entered as a specific lines within the block of text in the "
"``.json`` file. Invalid ``.json`` files will error out if the "
"syntax/formatting is incorrect."
msgstr ""

